comments: Zubac (LAC) maintains a collapsed forearm on Doncic's (DAL) side when marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Kleber (DAL) and Mann (LAC) engage and separate during the rebound.
Brunson (DAL) makes contact with Jackson's (LAC) body that affects his driving shot attempt.
Mann (LAC) dislodges the ball prior to incidental contact occurring with Doncic (DAL) on the rebound.
Brunson (DAL) makes marginal body contact with Jackson (LAC) after he retrieves the rebound.
Kleber (DAL) establishes himself in a screening position in Mann's (LAC) path and absorbs the body contact during the pick.
Finney-Smith (DAL) makes contact with Mann's (LAC) upper body, which affects his driving shot attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined that the foul called on Finney-Smith (DAL) did not meet the criteria for a flagrant foul.
Kleber (DAL) establishes himself in a screening position in Mann's (LAC) path and absorbs the contact during the pick.
Zubac (LAC) doesn't maintain a legal guarding position when he makes contact with Doncic's (DAL) arm on his driving shot attempt.
The Clippers call a timeout prior to any potential contact on the perimeter.
Brunson's (DAL) resting forearm makes contact with Mann's (LAC) elbow during his upward shooting motion.
Finney-Smith (DAL) engages for a rebounding position with Zubac (LAC), and the contact is marginal.
Doncic (DAL) makes incidental contact as he naturally releases from Zubac (LAC) at the end of his drive.
Jackson's (LAC) hand stays on the side of the ball during his dribble in the backcourt.
Brunson (DAL) does not make any contact as he attempts to commit a take foul on Jackson (LAC) in the backcourt.
Brunson (DAL) commits a take foul on Jackson (LAC).
